      "topic": "Asset Misappropriation — Inventory & Assets",
      "question": "A CFE is investigating potential inventory theft at a manufacturing warehouse. During the investigation, the CFE discovers that the perpetual inventory records show 10,000 units of raw materials on hand, but the physical count reveals only 7,500 units. The warehouse manager explains that the difference is due to normal shrinkage and evaporation of volatile materials. Which of the following procedures would be MOST effective in determining whether the shortage is due to theft versus legitimate shrinkage?",
      "options": [
        "Compare the current shrinkage percentage to historical shrinkage rates for similar volatile materials and industry benchmarks",
